Sarova Hotels in partnership with Tsavo Heritage Foundation recently launched the Tsavo Week celebrations at the Sarova Stanley ballroom. The week is an initiative aimed at bringing people together towards conserving the Tsavo ecosystem. Sarova managing director Jimi Kariuki presided over the event, attended by diplomats including Australian delegates. Tsavo Heritage Foundation and the Australian High Commission unveiled a plaque to remember Lt William Dartnell, an Australian who served in the British Army during the war in Taita Taveta.